2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with speech signals and proposes a method for separating and recognizing multiple speakers from a single speech sequence. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new objective function to improve the contrast between hidden vectors, which is a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with multiple speakers and proposes a method for recognizing their speech, which can be applied in social and information networks. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - Although the paper does not deal with computer vision, it is possible that the proposed method can be applied to visual speech recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision.
